      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="936-020B" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-936-020B-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-936-020B-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-936-020B-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Upon a Candle, inscrib'd to the R<hi rend="sup">t</hi> 08─Hon<hi rend="sup">bl</hi> 08 08── the Lady Carteret by D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Delany. F.T.C.D.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-936-020B-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-936-020B-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-936-020B-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-936-020B-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-936-020B-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-936-020B-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-1"> Of all th'·Inhabitants of Earth&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-2"> To Man alone I owe my Birth;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-3"> Tho the Cow, the Sheep, the Bee,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-4"> Are my Parents more than he.I (a virtue Strange &amp; rare)</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-5"> Make the fairest look more fair,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-6"> And my Self, what yet is rarer,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-7"> Growing older still grow fairer.Like Sots, alone I'm dull enough,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-8"> Doz'd with Smoak, &amp; smear'd with Snuff</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-9"> But amidst good Cheer and Wine,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-10"> I with double Lustre Shine.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-11"> Emblem of the fair am I,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-12"> Polish'd Neck, and radiant Eye;</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-13"> In my Eye my greatest Grace,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-14"> Emblem of the Cyclop Race;</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-15"> Metals I like them subdue,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-16"> Slave like them to Vulcan too.<gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/></l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-17"> Emblem of the lovesick Dame,</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-18"> That in silence feeds her Flame,</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-19"> Often aiding to impart,</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-20"> All the Secrets of her Heart.</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-21"> Emblem of a Monarck old,</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-22"> Wise, &amp; glorious to behold,</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-23"> Wasted he appears and pale,</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-24"> Watching for the publick Weal.</l><l n="25" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-25"> Various is my Shape and Hue,</l><l n="26" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-26"> Big like Bess, &amp; small like Sue,</l><l n="27" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-27"> Now brown and burnish'd like a Nut,</l><l n="28" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-28"> At other times a very slut;</l><l n="29" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-29"> Often fair, &amp; Soft, and tender,</l><l n="30" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-30"> Taper, tall, and Smooth, and Slender<gap/><gap/></l><l n="31" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-31"> But whatever be my Dress,</l><l n="32" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-32"> Greater be my Size or less,</l><l n="33" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-33"> Swelling be my Shape, or small,</l><l n="34" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-34"> Like thy self, I Shine in all.<gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/>Soon or late my Date is done:</l><l n="35" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-35"> As my Thread of Life is spun;</l><l n="36" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-36"> Yet to art <unclear>insthe</unclear> fatal thread,</l><l n="37" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-37"> Oft revives my drooping Head.<gap/><gap/></l><l n="38" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-38"> Clouded if my Face is seen,</l><l n="39" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-39"> My Complexion wan and green;</l><l n="40" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-40"> Languid like the lovesick Maid</l><l n="41" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-41"> Steel affords me present aid:</l><l n="42" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-42"> *·Dye, like Lovers as they Gaze,</l><l n="43" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-43"> Dye, for those I live to please;</l><l n="44" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-44"> Pine unpitied to my Urn,</l><l n="45" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-45"> Nor warm the Fair, for whom I burn;</l><l n="46" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-46"> Unpitied, unrelented too,</l><l n="47" xml:id="spp-936-020B-line-47"> Die, like those that look on you.936-020B   </l></lg></div>
